## Standing rules

- **Plan before executing** on any non-trivial task (Shift+Tab in Claude Code). Ask until 95% confident before acting.
- **Minimal targeted edits** when modifying existing files. Generate complete new files only on explicit ask ("write it", "generate", "create").
- **Skills > CLAUDE.md** for anything that doesn't need to fire every turn (progressive disclosure).
- **Watch context.** `/context` regularly. `/compact` at 60%, not 90%. `/clear` between unrelated tasks.
- **No bullet-point soup** in prose responses. Structure when it earns its place; otherwise paragraphs.

## Skill index

Skills live in `.claude/skills/` and auto-discover by frontmatter. Categories: `thinking/` (cognitive), `operating/` (how to work with Claude), domain-specific files at the top level. See `pitfalls.md` for anti-patterns. Invoke `skill-creator` to author a new skill from a successful run; invoke other meta-skills (e.g. `monetize-or-opensource`) when their triggers fire.
